<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.34.15.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">15</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<opener>
<address><addrLine>Elmwood, Neb. 68349</addrLine></address>
<dateline>Apr. 29, 1970
</dateline>
<salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>

<p>We watched and listened to your interview on the Dick Cavett show, and you were just great!</p>

<p>It's been some time since we enjoyed viewing a program to the e3xtent we did that one of yours. Our son, John, came in from the field weary after disking and stayed up to watch every minute of your show. That, in addition to a full day at school, meant he had to fight to stay awake.</p>

<p>We just hope we can see the other parts of the program you had taped.</p>

<p>You started your college teaching career kind of late in life, how about beginning a TV show - a conversation with Neihardt - at age 90?</p>

<p>May God bless.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Sincerely,</salute>
<signed>The Marion Weizels</signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
